<font color="#FF0000">DIFFERENT MEANINGS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Nov 14 23:56:33 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My purpose in starting this thread was to encourage some to talk about feelings of low worth, guilt, depression and things that usually are no more than haunting myths.<br><br>
In order to feel bad.. you have to have some values..and a conscience.  It is because we subscribe to some list of good things that we persever.  We often believe, falsly, but none the less, believe that we didn't do enough.<br><br>
People who have done NOTHING and have NO VALUES are the ones most likely to criticise US.  They get some sick buzz from making us react to their voices.  All in all it is a control issue.. they like to control us and they do so by making us angry.<br><br>
Somehow, I feel stronger when weak people come against me with their impotent slurs.  When I ignore them or laugh to myself.. they come unglued.<br><br>
I will always feel bad for having killed children..not saving every evacuee..and for watching my brothers die while I continued to live...but I will not feel bad because of some mentally ill traitor and his babblings.<br><br>
Instead, I choose to find glory and honor in my surviving brothers.  I want to sing of their deeds.  I want to hold up my head in their presence.  And I always will!<br><br>
MTF<br><br>

